
# GalleryShowcase PRD Document

## 1. Product Overview
GalleryShowcase is a visually stunning image display platform designed to showcase photography, artwork, and digital media in an elegant, responsive interface.

## 2. Core Features

### 2.1 Responsive Gallery Grid
- Dynamic masonry-style layout that adapts to any screen size
- Smooth image loading with lazy-loading technology
- Multiple view modes (grid, carousel, fullscreen)

### 2.2 Image Presentation
- High-resolution display with zoom capabilities
- EXIF data display (for photography)
- Color palette extraction from images
- Social sharing integration

### 2.3 User Experience
- Keyboard navigation support
- Dark/light mode toggle
- Customizable transition animations
- Accessibility features (alt text, screen reader support)

## 3. Technical Specifications

### 3.1 Frontend Requirements
- React.js with TypeScript
- CSS-in-JS styling (styled-components)
- Intersection Observer API for lazy loading
- WebP image format support with fallbacks

### 3.2 Performance
- Image compression pipeline
- CDN integration
- Progressive loading indicators
- Cache optimization strategies

### 3.3 Backend Requirements (Optional)
- Node.js API for image metadata
- Cloud storage integration (AWS S3 or equivalent)
- Rate limiting for API calls

## 4. UI/UX Details

### 4.1 Layout Components
- Header with branding and navigation
- Filter/sort controls
- Main gallery container
- Image detail modal
- Footer with credits and links

### 4.2 Interactive Elements
- Hover effects on gallery items
- Smooth scrolling behavior
- Touch gesture support for mobile
- Loading state animations

## 5. Quality Assurance

### 5.1 Testing Requirements
- Cross-browser compatibility
- Performance benchmarking
- Mobile responsiveness testing
- Accessibility validation

## 6. Future Enhancements
- User authentication for private galleries
- AI-powered image tagging
- 3D gallery viewing modes
- Collaborative annotation features
